			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Lineup - What are you using and how?<a name="72190"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 19 05 12:25 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I agree with most of what is said on HO's. However, they are  two-edged sword.
<br />

<br />
The groups I am in are often undersized and pushing it for the mob level. (a group of 3 vs a 2up yelo named is a definite push)
<br />

<br />
On the one hand, ho's are powerful and its difficult to complete a really tuff fight successfully if you don't use them. On the other hand, maintaining 2-3 runes on the mt, and keeping the mob debuffed is paramount as well. If you wait on HO timing you may be late renewing a crucial cast....once behind in healing or debuffing, its hard to recover in a tuff fight. Your healer burns power too fast with direct heals. I occoasionally count on HO progression to supply crucial casts...if you don't get the HO you were trying for and can't switch it, sometimes that bites you in the a$. When it works, its really cool tho...constant HO's supplying the crucial casts as well really are nice. 
<br />

<br />
Thats whats good about the individual HO's discussed above. Often many classes can choose and control individual HO's to supply those crucial casts.
<br />

<br />
If I end up with aggro, or am tanking, I get agility maxed and parry maxed as soon as possible. While we aren't ideal tanks,  after a mob has burnt his power, if I have parry and agility buffed I take very little damage.
<br />

<br />
Otherwise, I usually have haste and atk buffs up. Thats 4 concentration. The choice then is debuff the mob or a 3rd party buff (in groups). I make the choice based number of mobs vs number of pc. If a group of 6 with 3/4 melees is attacking on named, I buff the party, the multiplier effect give the greatest benefit. 
<br />

<br />
If its 10 mobs verse a small group, I debuff the mobs, using the same logic.
<br />

<br />
As far as offensive skills/songs that dont require concentration, I go light early while the tank builds aggro, and pour it on late, as long as I don't deplete my power any more than the group average.
<br />

<br />
I should mention I sometimes box a cleric with my dirge (never in large groups tho and only with friends). HO timing/execution is really simplified when you are running 2 toons.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
